  "texts": [
    "For instance, they used random cropping and Gaussian tinting techniques to increase the diversity of the images in the data set.",
    "After training and testing, they also composed a separate challenge data set, which applied the data-augmentation policies to images from categories that their model had difficulty identifying accurately, including female individuals, older adults, and individuals with darker skin.",
    "The MORPH data set lacks images of older adults, so adding additional images was effective in addressing representation and evaluation bias in the data set [5].",
    "The data augmentation policies would be randomly applied to these images as they were loaded during training [37].",
    "This method to augment the training data was effective, as the overall MAE fell from 4.62 to 4.21, with a final MAE of 4.13 for male individuals and 4.90 for female individuals."
